==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[Μυκήναι]]''' (''Mykenae'') "[[Mycenae]]", the name of the Ancient Greek city, from '''[[Μυκήνη]]''' (''Mykene''), in Greek mythology a [[Nymph]] who lived around Mycenae.

===Adjective===
'''Mycenaean'''
#Of or relating to ancient Mycenae or its inhabitants.
#Of or relating to the [[Mycenaean civilization]]. 
#Of or relating to the Ancient Greek dialect written in the [[Linear B]] [[syllabary]].

===Noun===
'''Mycenaean'''
#A native or inhabitant of Mycenae.
#[[Mycenaean Greek]]. 

===Translations===
*Greek: [[Μυκηναικός]] (''Mykenaekos'') {{m}}